comment: Loved your video but I wish, when you provided the quote about her being financially independent of Johnny, that even though she claimed to have donated the entirety of the divorce settlement, there is now indesputable proof she never donated any of it (outside of what Johnny donated on her behalf, $200k). In fact, her lawyer admitted to media that she was unable to donate the money because Depp sued her (13 months after the final installment of the $7m was paid to her) and that she intended to eventually honor her pledge. But a letter from the CHLA in June of 2019 told her they only received the first $100k that Johnny sent and nothing since so wanted confirmation If she was going to donate the rest of the promised 3.4m or if the pledge would be unfulfilled. They got no response from Amber. The appeal in the UK showed documents that anonymous donation were made in her behalf or were recommended by her to the ACLU but did not count towards her $3.5m pledge. Then an unsigned, undated letter from Amber to the ACLU was provided saying she would pay the money off in 10 years but no payment plan was drafted and, even though they say it was made in 2016, there was no further donation made. (outside of Johnny's initial $100k amount and a $350k donation made before Johnny gave her any money, she can't donate the settlement if she doesn't have it yet, in the last 4 years since she apparently made that promise letter) This still doesn't explain how she was going to fulfill her pledge to the CHLA. She lied about the donations to get clout and favor and continues to lie now trying to cover up her initial lie. She was very clear she had already donated the full amount, meaning she kept none of it but now we know she kept it all.
